http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Body-of-migrant-worker-found/article13983811.ece

: The body of a migrant worker with injury to the throat was found in his rented house at Pallikkunnu here late night on January 4.The deceased has been identified as Rabeendra Bala (23), son of Ramakrishna, hailing from Bidhan Pally in Jalpaiguri district in West Bengal. The body with slit throat was found in a pool of blood by his colleagues who were living in the house. The police said that a knife was recovered from the spot. They immediately informed the police. The police said that the deceased had been living in the house for the past 18 months.